  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ghana Mushroom Growers&#x2019; Needs Assessment Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Challenges: MGA is at an embryonic stage of development. There is no clear data on its strengths, weaknesses or organisational developmental needs to meets its strategic objectives &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#xA2;No data on the effectiveness or otherwise of MGA in meeting the expressed/implied membership needs and how to achieve its aspiration of becoming the &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2DC;one stop shop&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122; of support for small scale mushroom growers &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#xA2;Necessity of reviewing MGA/membership for data on capacity building/technical development needs to build a case for international funding to meet these needs &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#xA2;Need for better co-ordination and synergy between MGA/members and key industry stakeholders and Government initiatives. Objectives &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#xA2;Review MGA, its overall business strategy in line with its stated objectives &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#xA2;Identify the capacity building and technical developmental needs of MGA and members &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#xA2;Identify opportunities for membership and service expansion nationally &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#xA2;Identify strategic stakeholders and local programmes MGA can participate in (creating synergies) Outcomes *Clear data on what is working well and what is not (gaps and priorities) *A full report with recommendations outlining the training and capacity needs of MGA and membership *An action plan with milestones within set timeframe and for expanding, improving and strengthening MGA</narrative>
  </description>
